<div id="review_420590160" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/420590160" />
    <a title="Jay Schutt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13086055-jay-schutt"><img alt="Jay Schutt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1539008920p2/13086055.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/420590160?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jay Schutt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jay Schutt" href="/user/show/13086055-jay-schutt">Jay Schutt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780440241539" href="/book/show/1125055.The_King_of_Torts">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13086055-jay-schutt?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13086055-jay-schutt?shelf=legal-thriller">legal-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer420590160" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17602810642667783645">Money, money, money. Greed, greed, greed. This book is about the destructive power of greed and how fast one can fall from the top. While reading this, I felt like the hammer was going to drop at any minute. When it did, I felt gratified that the &quot;easy come, easy go&quot; scenario was played out to its fullest. Very well written, of course, by Grisham.</span>
  <span id="freeText17602810642667783645" style="display:none">Money, money, money. Greed, greed, greed. This book is about the destructive power of greed and how fast one can fall from the top. While reading this, I felt like the hammer was going to drop at any minute. When it did, I felt gratified that the "easy come, easy go" scenario was played out to its fullest. Very well written, of course, by Grisham.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17602810642667783645" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
