        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer326091972" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7998440305431066300">As a lover of legal thrillers, I try to read all of John Crisham&apos;s books. This book was really interesting and such a page turner from the very beginning: there is not any moment of boredom for readers, nor anything unconvincing! I got more and more intrigued as the story went on, I was constantly thinking about our main man - Clay Carter - even when I am not reading. The book introduced me to a new (and probably very miniscule (in terms of size) world) of mass tort lawyers and pharmaceutical in</span>
  <span id="freeText7998440305431066300" style="display:none">As a lover of legal thrillers, I try to read all of John Crisham's books. This book was really interesting and such a page turner from the very beginning: there is not any moment of boredom for readers, nor anything unconvincing! I got more and more intrigued as the story went on, I was constantly thinking about our main man - Clay Carter - even when I am not reading. The book introduced me to a new (and probably very miniscule (in terms of size) world) of mass tort lawyers and pharmaceutical industry: it is incredible It was a nice escape from my daily routine, and something to look forward to at the end of a long day. I would recommend it highly if you like feasible mystery and adventure but in a real world. </span>
